parameters: \n<Deer Man>\c[1]While you were wandering, trying to get the garden doors open, I took a look out the window and noticed the state of the fire ladder.
\n<Deer Man>\c[1]I understand it wouldn’t stay iced over for long in case of a fire, but it still serves as quite the safety issue regardless, wouldn’t you say?
\n<Deer Man>\c[1]I was merely talking for my own sake at this time but...
\n<Deer Man>\c[1]If you understand me, you don’t have much time left to make your exit.
\n<Deer Man>\c[1]Let’s see... You’re wearing gloves, you should be fine. Take this with you.
He hands over a\c[4] Hot Kettle\c[0].
\n<Deer Man>\c[1]Consider it a consolation for Miss Martino and Mr. Malthus’s behavior tonight.
\n<Deer Man>\c[1]Those two hold their own personal agendas in higher regard than library rules.
\n<Mitch>You’re a lifesaver. Thank you so much, um... uh...
\n<Mr. Lane>\c[1]I will be returning to my desk now. Be sure to keep your guard up until you’re sure that you are back where you belong.

\n<Mitch>If she wants to see me, she can before I go. You’ve done enough.
\n<Mr. Lane>\c[1]In that case, I will continue my archival work. Best of luck to you.
